    <question>
        <prompt>The American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) was founded in the 1920s primarily to:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Support Prohibition enforcement</option>
            <option letter="b">Defend constitutional rights and civil liberties</option>
            <option letter="c">Promote women's suffrage</option>
            <option letter="d">Advocate for labor unions</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The ACLU was established in 1920 to defend constitutional rights, particularly First Amendment freedoms. It played crucial roles in significant cases of the 1920s, including the Scopes "Monkey" Trial and cases involving free speech, helping protect civil liberties during a period of increased government restrictions.</explanation>
    </question>
